org.eclipse.keyple.transaction

Class SeSelectionRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.keyple.transaction.SeSelectionRequest

  • public class SeSelectionRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    The SeSelectionRequest class combines a SeSelector with additional helper methods useful to the selection process done in SeSelection.

    This class may also be extended to add particular features specific to a SE family.

      • setMatchingClass

        protected final void setMatchingClass(java.lang.Class<? extends MatchingSe> matchingClass)
        The matchingClass is the MatchingSe class or one of its extensions

        It is used in SeSelection to determine what kind of MatchingSe is to be instantiated. This method must be called in the classes that extend SeSelector in order to specify the expected class derived from MatchingSe in return to the selection process.

        Parameters:
        matchingClass - the expected class for this SeSelector

      • setSelectionClass

        protected final void setSelectionClass(java.lang.Class<? extends SeSelectionRequest> selectionClass)
        The selectionClass is the SeSelector class or one of its extensions

        It is used in SeSelection to determine what kind of SeSelector is to be used as argument to the matchingClass constructor. This method must be called in the classes that extend SeSelector in order to specify the expected class derived from SeSelector used as an argument to derived form of MatchingSe.

        Parameters:
        selectionClass - the argument for the constructor of the matchingClass

      • getSelectionClass

        protected final java.lang.Class<? extends SeSelectionRequest> getSelectionClass()

        the current selectionClass

      • addApduRequest

        protected final void addApduRequest(ApduRequest apduRequest)
        Add an additional ApduRequest to be executed after the selection process if it succeeds.

        If more than one ApduRequest is added, all will be executed in the order in which they were added.

        Parameters:
        apduRequest - an ApduRequest
